Cache expanded mode variants

Consider a situation where we have a back reference to a parent mode
with variants:

    var LIST = {
      className: 'list',
      variants: [
        { begin: /\(/, end: /\)/ },
        { begin: /\[/, end: /\]/ }
      ],
      contains: [BODY]
    };

    BODY.contains = [LIST];

After LISTs variants are expanded when compiling its own parent,
BODY still holds a reference to the old non-expanded LIST, and it
will be expanded again into new copies when BODY is compiled, which
leads to undesired effects.

The new function `expand_variants` will expand mode's variants and
cache the result to be reused next time it's called for the mode.
